WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#92: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:65:
+	BUG_ON(!child);

BUG() or BUG_ON() should be avoided totally.
Use WARN() and WARN_ON() instead, and handle the "impossible"
error condition as gracefully as possible.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/deprecated.html#bug-and-bug-on

WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#136: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:109:
+		BUG_ON(rc);

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'initial != iov->total'
#226: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:199:
+	if (initial > iov->total ||
+	    (!(iov->cap & PCI_SRIOV_CAP_VFM) && (initial != iov->total)))

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'nr_virtfn > initial'
#230: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:203:
+	if (nr_virtfn < 0 || nr_virtfn > iov->total ||
+	    (!(iov->cap & PCI_SRIOV_CAP_VFM) && (nr_virtfn > initial)))

CHECK:PARENTHESIS_ALIGNMENT: Alignment should match open parenthesis
#270: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:243:
+		rc = sysfs_create_link(&dev->dev.kobj,
+					&pdev->dev.kobj, "dep_link");

WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#342: FILE: drivers/pci/iov.c:414:
+	BUG_ON(dev->sriov->nr_virtfn);

CHECK:AVOID_EXTERNS: extern prototypes should be avoided in .h files
#433: FILE: include/linux/pci.h:1213:
+extern int pci_enable_sriov(struct pci_dev *dev, int nr_virtfn);

Function prototypes don't need to be declared extern in .h
files.  It's assumed by the compiler and is unnecessary.

CHECK:AVOID_EXTERNS: extern prototypes should be avoided in .h files
#434: FILE: include/linux/pci.h:1214:
+extern void pci_disable_sriov(struct pci_dev *dev);

CHECK:LINE_SPACING: Please use a blank line after function/struct/union/enum declarations
#440: FILE: include/linux/pci.h:1220:
+}
+static inline void pci_disable_sriov(struct pci_dev *dev)

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

